FBIS3-44068 "drafr015_c_94025" FBIS-AFR-94-015 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Saudi Imam Arrives in Cape Town 23 Jan MB2201202994 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0902 GMT 22 Jan 94 MB2201202994 Johannesburg SAPA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Cape Town Jan 22 SAPA--The imam of the Grand Mosque in Mecca, Saudi Arabia, will arrive in Cape Town on Sunday, SABC [South African Broadcasting Corporation] radio news reports. A spokesman for the Muslim Judicial Council said Shaykh Muhammad al-Subayl's visit had become possible because of the political changes in the country. The imam would visit South Africa as an act of goodwill and would take part in the tri-centenary celebrations of Islam in South Africa, the spokesman said.
